<br>
This is a link to dex tests showing how we are underperforming w/o dex buffs from items.<br>
<br>
THE problem is that buffs are not additive to your defensive skills. Buffs create a MULTIPLIER which is then multiplied by your base chance to evade (5%) so maxing out your dex/quick is only going to marginally increase your evade chance. I can't imagine any level of buffs even from a full spec buff shaman which would create a multiplier of 200% (doubling evade chance). SO I would say even with max buffs your evade chance wont exceed 10%. While the same buffs on an assassin with base chance to evade of 35% will bring his evade chance over 50% (which is why they put in the 50% evade cap). IMO terrible way to design the evade formula.<br>
<br>
Parry is calculated in a similar manner the difference being that you can control your base parry chance with spec but those who choose to spec 2 in parry will notice barely any effects from +dex buffs on their parry chance while those who spec 17 parry will show more bonus from dex buffs.<br>
<br>
I am planning on respeccing out of mastery of parry just because I want to get avoid pain but I need another 1.4 million realm points to get both so I would rather have avoid pain now instead of later. So its something to think about when you are choosing how high to spec in parry because if you don't plan on getting mastery of parry then you might just leave your parry low anyway because w/o mastery of parry your parry chance is going to be sad.<br>
<br>
